    "body": "To prevent copy theft. \r\n\r\nIf the EEA wants to publicly redistribute Lighthouse with a closed source license, then they should contact the Lighthouse team for a specific license for that. I'm sure they would be willing to accommodate such that the EEA doesn't solely profit from the efforts of the Lighthouse team. \r\n\r\nOtherwise, they are still free to use Lighthouse for private use with modifications without publishing their source code, as long as they don't distribute it publicly, AFAIK. \r\n\r\nLicensing didn't kill cpp-ethereum, it is still alive under a different name: https://github.com/ethereum/aleth\r\n\r\nEdit: I'm not part of Lighthouse team, but we use GPLv3 @ https://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm",
