    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I can't speak for the EEA, I can only speak as someone who stood by and witnessed certain events. I have no idea if they'd want to use Lighthouse or not, and I'll leave that up to them. I was just using the situation of the GPL licensing debacle on CPP-Ethereum (which spawned the EEA) as an example of how copyleft can work against itself. \r\n\r\nAlso I'm using it as a basis for deciding whether I want to contribute to Lighthouse or not. I really like the approach your team is taking in general (notwithstanding the licensing,) and before I give my support and volunteer time to improve an open-source project, I make sure my values line up with the the team so that my interested contributions don't end up working against the larger team goal.\r\n\r\nI think I have my answer, so unless you want to discuss further, feel free to close this. :)",
